@ZombieSloth 
After installation you should have gotten 3 shortcuts to each of the games. If they are not there then check inside the program files. 

@dgak23

You could try reinstailling it again then uninstalling it. Or repairing it. But if you don't want to spend the time doing that then you could delete the game from your program dir and (if your picky) then manually remove its registry keys or use some type of reg cleaner.

If you have trouble running the installer, 

actually open up the disc, not just autorun and use the installer there, 

try running the installer as admin,

try turning off UAC then installing, 

or try using winrar to extract the .iso and then installing it.

@People with problems, don't expect me to bother to help you if you can't even bother to list your system specs and maybe some of the issues you are encountering along with what program you are using to mount. 

@Skulldragon

Glad the game worked for you, although you don't have to act like a douche as that comment about sharing seems to make you out as. 

+1 for having a 6950 like me by the way ;)
